                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/02/2003&nbsp;: 05:43:29 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><i>Originally posted by Zeezel</i><br /><br />...but with all the aggro kiting i'm doing now, a faster horse seems really handy, i'm wondering if the 30k horse may be a wise purchase<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br />As posted up above (but worth reinforcing) agro kiting whilst mounted can be dangerous. When casting on the mob you will be waiting whilst it comes into range, and then casting. Depending on the mob you may find that they are nearly within melee range before the spells completes (depending on the spell too), so that slow startup can mean that even with the fastest horse you still get pounded every time.<br /><br />I shudder to think of the results if you cast dooming to snare a Nettling Wraith (fast) in PoN whilst on horseback. I think it's fair to say that if it didn't stick you'd be dead or feigned on very low health.<br /><br />The only reason to get one of the cheaper horses (up to 30kpp) is for agro control. Invest in a pair of Jboots instead :)<br /><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><i>Originally posted by Xero</i><br /><br />The 30k horse should run about Jboot's speed, although it is good to have one, for the medding when you are running from the mob.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br />Common belief but sadly wrong. You don't gain mana whilst moving or casting. There is literally no benefit to having a cheap horse unless you use it for agro mitigation in outside zones.<br /><br />Regards<br /><br />Rhys<br /><br /><img src="http://www.clement-evans.co.uk/xatan/xatan-eyes-bordered.jpg" border="0"></span></font></td>
